From: Walker Chen <walker.chen@starfivetech.com>
Date: Mon, 12 Jun 2023 21:21:45 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 077/121] dmaengine: dw-axi-dmac: Drop unused print message

Removed printing information which is not related to StarFive
platform.

Signed-off-by: Walker Chen <walker.chen@starfivetech.com>
---
 drivers/dma/dw-axi-dmac/dw-axi-dmac-platform.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/dma/dw-axi-dmac/dw-axi-dmac-platform.c b/drivers/dma/dw-axi-dmac/dw-axi-dmac-platform.c
index dd02f84e404d..d75802a57eea 100644
--- a/drivers/dma/dw-axi-dmac/dw-axi-dmac-platform.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/dw-axi-dmac/dw-axi-dmac-platform.c
@@ -522,7 +522,7 @@ static void dw_axi_dma_set_hw_channel(struct axi_dma_chan *chan, bool set)
 	unsigned long reg_value, val;
 
 	if (!chip->apb_regs) {
-		dev_err(chip->dev, "apb_regs not initialized\n");
+		dev_dbg(chip->dev, "apb_regs not initialized\n");
 		return;
 	}
 
